        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 5:40PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 540 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms 21 miles northeast of Sheridan, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Leiter.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
